# Git commit messages

- **Language:** Write every commit message in **English** only (title and body). Do not use Serbian, German, or other languages in commits.
- **Title:** Short, imperative mood (e.g. `fix contact form validation`, `docs: update README`).
- **Body:** Use when needed for context; keep complete sentences and stay in English.

```text
✅ docs: refresh README for Next 14 stack
✅ fix: show consent error in active locale

❌ docs: ažuriran README
❌ fix: poruka na nemačkom
```
